    <b>What's Sai Phalkhi Story? </b> <br />
    During the days between 1910 to 1918, When Sai Baba was living in Dwarakamai (Masjid), he used to sleep in Chawadi for every alternate nights. And these alternate night was prefaced by "PALKHI" procession.
    These processions were carried out with all royal appurtenance and Sai Baba was accompanied from Dwarakamai to Chawdi.<br />
    Even Now, this Palkhi procession continues with the same excitement and veneration in every Thursday, it starts from Samadhi Mandir and proceeds to Dwarakamai Masjid and then it goes to Chawdi and then returns to Samadhi Mandir.
